article.headline: Georgia State 71
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Leonard Mendez scored 21 points to lead Georgia State past Northeastern 71-65 on Wednesday night. Ryan McBride's 3-pointer with 3:54 left in the game capped an 11-0 run that gave the Panthers (9-17 overall, 5-11 Colonial Athletic Association) a 57-49 lead. Eugene Spates' layup with 1:46 left brought Northeastern (9-18, 7-9) within 59-55. Mendez then hit a jumper and a pair of free throws during a 6-0 run that stretched the Panthers' lead to 65-55. The Panthers led 67-57 before Northeastern got 3-pointers from Bennet Davis and Spates in the final minute along with a couple of free throws by Matt Janning to pull within 67-65 with with 8 seconds left, but the Huskies could not score again. Spates led Northeastern with 16 points. Lance Perique scored 19 for Georgia State.
